heading_context: Check if you're eligible for the Warm Home Discount
chunks.html_content:
You do not need to apply for the Warm Home Discount. You’ll be paid automatically by your energy supplier.

Use this service to find out:

  • if you’re eligible for the scheme 
  • what to do if you did not get a letter about the Warm Home Discount but think you may be eligible

The Warm Home Discount is not available in Northern Ireland. Find out about the Affordable Warmth scheme instead.

heading_context: Check if you're eligible for the Warm Home Discount
chunks.html_content:
Start now

You’ll need:

  • the name of your electricity supplier

  • details of any benefits you receive

You’ll also need to know the size and age of your property and what type of property it is.

If your property has an energy performance certificate (EPC), you can enter your postcode to fill in these details. 

If your property does not have an EPC, you can find these details on property documents, like your tenancy agreement or insurance paperwork.
